title.narrative: Sahel Women's Empowerment and Demographics Project

description.narrative: The development objective is to increase women and adolescent girls’ empowerment and their access to quality reproductive, childand maternal health services in selected areas of the participating countries, including the Recipients' territory, and to improveregional knowledge generation and sharing as well as regional capacity and coordination.

condition.narrative: AU Financing Agreement, Schedule 2, Section I, C: The Recipient shall not later than sixty (60) days after the Effective Date,prepare and submit an operations manual, satisfactory to the Association (Project Operations Manual) and, thereafter, carry out theProject in accordance with said Project Operations Manual.

AU Financing Agreement, Schedule 2, Section IV, 1: The Recipient shall not later than three (3) months after the EffectiveDeadline, recruit or assign a finance officer for the Project, all in accordance with the Procurement Regulations.

Cameroon Financing Agreement, Schedule 2, Section I, A (d): The Recipient maintain, throughout Project implementation, andpublicize the availability of a grievance mechanism, in form and substance satisfactory to the Association, to hear and determinefairly and in good faith all complaints raised in relation to the Project, and take all measures necessary to implement thedeterminations made by such mechanism in a manner satisfactory to the Association.

Cameroon Financing Agreement, Schedule 2, Section I, C: The Recipient shall not later than sixty (60) days after the EffectiveDate, prepare and submit an operations manual, satisfactory to the Association (Project Operations Manual) and, thereafter, carryout the Project in accordance with said Project Operations Manual.

Cameroon Financing Agreement, Schedule 2, Section IV, 1 (a): recruit a financial management officer, an accountant for the Project,and an internal auditor, all with qualifications, experience and terms of reference, satisfactory to the Association within 3months of effectiveness.

Cameroon Financing Agreement, Schedule 2, Section IV, 1 (b): develop and submit to the Association, an administrative and financialmanagement manual of procedures, satisfactory to the Association within 3 months of effectiveness.
Cameroon Financing Agreement, Schedule 2, Section IV, 1 (c): acquire and install a computerized accounting system, satisfactory tothe Association within 3 months of effectiveness.

Cameroon Financing Agreement, Schedule 2, Section IV, 1(d): prepare and submit to the Association terms of reference for externalauditor, in form and substance satisfactory to the Association, and thereafter, recruit an independent external auditor inaccordance with the Procurement Regulations within 3 months of effectiveness.

ECOWAS Financing Agreement, Schedule 2, Section I, E: the Recipient shall cause the Project Implementing Entity, no later than onemonth after the Effective Date, to enter into the Agreement for the Provision of Technical Assistance with a selected UN agencyunder terms and conditions approved by the Association, as further described in the Project Operations Manual (“Agreement for theProvision of Technical Assistance”).

ECOWAS Financing Agreement, Schedule 2, Section IV, 1(a): recruit an accountant or a finance officer with qualifications,experience and terms of reference, satisfactory to the Association within 3 months of effectiveness.

ECOWAS Financing Agreement, Schedule 2, Section IV, 1(b): revise the financial management manual of the Original Project to includethis Project, in form and substance satisfactory to the Association within 3 months of effectiveness.
ECOWAS Financing Agreement, Schedule 2, Section IV, 1(c): recruit an external auditor for the Project in accordance with theprovisions of the Procurement Regulations within 3 months of effectiveness.

Finance Agreement :ALL COUNTRIES - Adoption of the Project Operational Manual | Description :On or before one month after theEffectiveness date, the Recipient shall adopt the Project Operational Manual in form and substance satisfactory to the Association

Finance Agreement :ALL COUNTRIES - Set up of Project Implementation Units | Description :On or before one month after theEffectiveness date, the Recipient shall set up a Project Implementation Unit, in form and substance satisfactory to the Association
Finance Agreement :ALL COUNTRIES - Sign agreement with UNFPA | Description :Signing the TA agreement with UNFPA, not later than onemonth after effectiveness

Finance Agreement :Adoption of the Project Operational Manual | Description :On or before one month after the Effectiveness Date,the Recipient shall adopt the Project Operational Manual in form and substance satisfactory to the Association. | Due Date:31-Jul-2015

Finance Agreement :Set up of Project Implementation Unit of National Steering Committee | Description :On or before one month afterthe Effectiveness date, create and establish the Project Implementation Unit and the National Steering Committee in form andsubstance satisfactory to the Association | Due Date :31-Jul-2015
Finance Agreement :Sign agreement with UNFPA | Description :Signing the TA agreement with UNFPA, not later than two months aftereffectiveness

Finance Agreement :WAHO - Recruit one additional Accountant dedicated to the new project | Description :Schedule 2.Section I.A.1.On or before three months after the Effective Date, the Recipient shall appoint and assign to the Project Implementation Unit anadditional accountant with terms of reference, experience and skills acceptable to the Association, as further detailed in theProject Operations Manual and in accordance with the provisions of Section III of this Schedule. Due Date :30-Jan-2016

Finance Agreement :WAHO - Recruitment of the external auditor acceptable to IDA | Description :On or before three months after theEffective Date, the Recipient shall hire an external auditor, with terms of reference, experience and skills acceptable to theAssociation. | Due Date :30-Dec-2016

Finance Agreement :WAHO - Representative at the Regional Steering Committee | Description :WAHO shall appoint not later than onemonth after the Effective Date and thereafter maintain throughout the period of Project implementation its representative in theRegional Steering Committee to provide overall regional guidance and oversight for the Project and to participate in thesemi-annual meetings. | Due Date :18-May-2015

Finance Agreement :WAHO - WAHO Steering Committee | Description :WAHO shall establish no later than one month after the EffectiveDate and thereafter maintain the WAHO Steering Committee to provide guidance and oversight for the Project and hold semi-annualreviews of performance and implementation planning. | Due Date :30-Nov-2015

Guinea Financing Agreement, Schedule 2, Section I, A (d): The Recipient shall not later than sixty (60) days after the EffectiveDate, ensure that the Project Implementation Plan is fully staffed, and specifically recruit the key staff, including acoordinator, a financial management specialist, a procurement specialist, an accountant and a monitoring and evaluation specialist,all in accordance with the provisions of the Procurement Regulations.

Guinea Financing Agreement, Schedule 2, Section I, C: The Recipient shall not later than sixty (60) days after the Effective Date,prepare and submit an operations manual, satisfactory to the Association (Project Operations Manual) and, thereafter, carry out theProject in accordance with said Project Operations Manual,

Guinea Financing Agreement, Schedule 2, Section IV, 1(a): recruit a financial management officer, an accountant for the Project,and an internal auditor, all with qualifications, experience and terms of reference, satisfactory to the Association within 3months of effectiveness.
